This Simplified Chinese localization includes:
Cultural Adaptations:
Naruto terminology: 写轮眼 (Sharingan), 万花筒 (Mangekyo), 永恒万花筒写轮眼 (Eternal Mangekyo Sharingan), 鼬 (Itachi), 斑 (Madara)
Chinese comic terms: 对话框 (speech bubbles), 分镜 (panels), 拟声拟态词 (SFX)
Platform awareness: References to Bilibili Comics, Tencent Anime, and other Chinese manga platforms
Technical Considerations:
Writing direction: 横排 (horizontal) and 竖排 (vertical) text support for Japanese manga
Typography: Chinese font considerations for Simplified Chinese characters (Noto Sans SC)
Regional variants: Distinguishes between 简体 (Simplified) and 繁体 (Traditional) Chinese OCR modes
Linguistic Features:
Formal register: Uses standard polite Chinese throughout (~中, ~了, ~吗)
Onomatopoeia: Chinese equivalents for Japanese SFX (扑通扑通, 砰, 咔嚓, etc.)
Tech terminology: Standard Chinese UI terms (缓存, 覆盖层, 激活, etc.)
UX Localization:
Concise phrasing: Natural Chinese brevity (e.g., "点击激活" vs. "Click to activate")
Status indicators: Clear, direct status messages
Error handling: Polite but informative error messages using standard Chinese error conventions
The file maintains structural parity with the other language files while providing culturally authentic Chinese manga community terminology and proper handling of Japanese content consumption in Chinese-speaking regions.